Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on training a robot to be curious and learn in a real-time, human-in-the-loop training scenario onboard a drone. This falls under the domain of robotics and control.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep reinforcement learning to train the curiosity agent, which is a subfield of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with training an agent to learn in a simulated environment, which is a core area of artificial intelligence research.
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper involves training an object detection algorithm onboard a drone, which is a computer vision task.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with controlling the motion of a drone and training an agent to learn in a real-time, human-in-the-loop scenario, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
